Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Banco Santander Decline

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-26T21:59:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-grupo-galicia-ledesma-saai.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 5 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.4 percent to 3,268.55.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  ,  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value, dropped 0.7 percent to 14.05 pesos as prices fell
for some Argentine sovereign bonds, which signals lower value
for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  Banco Santander Rio SA (BRIO)  , a unit of  Spain ’s Banco
Santander, fell 0.8 percent to 12.80 pesos, after the parent
company said in a filing to regulators that its Argentine unit
had started procedures to seek authorization for the sale of
shares. The amount to be sold hasn’t been fixed yet, Santander
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
